rule_ids.help: Elements must only use supported ARIA attributes
rule_ids.description: Ensure an element's role supports its ARIA attributes

rule_ids.help: ARIA role should be appropriate for the element
rule_ids.description: Ensure role attribute has an appropriate value for the element

rule_ids.help: ARIA commands must have an accessible name
rule_ids.description: Ensure every ARIA button, link and menuitem has an accessible name

rule_ids.help: ARIA dialog and alertdialog nodes should have an accessible name
rule_ids.description: Ensure every ARIA dialog and alertdialog node has an accessible name

rule_ids.help: ARIA hidden element must not be focusable or contain focusable elements
rule_ids.description: Ensure aria-hidden elements are not focusable nor contain focusable elements

rule_ids.help: ARIA input fields must have an accessible name
rule_ids.description: Ensure every ARIA input field has an accessible name

rule_ids.help: Elements must only use permitted ARIA attributes
rule_ids.description: Ensure ARIA attributes are not prohibited for an element's role

rule_ids.help: Required ARIA attributes must be provided
rule_ids.description: Ensure elements with ARIA roles have all required ARIA attributes

rule_ids.help: Certain ARIA roles must contain particular children
rule_ids.description: Ensure elements with an ARIA role that require child roles contain them

rule_ids.help: Certain ARIA roles must be contained by particular parents
rule_ids.description: Ensure elements with an ARIA role that require parent roles are contained by them

rule_ids.help: ARIA roles used must conform to valid values
rule_ids.description: Ensure all elements with a role attribute use a valid value

rule_ids.help: ARIA attributes must conform to valid names
rule_ids.description: Ensure attributes that begin with aria- are valid ARIA attributes

rule_ids.help: ARIA attributes must conform to valid values
rule_ids.description: Ensure all ARIA attributes have valid values

rule_ids.help: Buttons must have discernible text
rule_ids.description: Ensure buttons have discernible text

rule_ids.help: Elements must meet minimum color contrast ratio thresholds
rule_ids.description: Ensure the contrast between foreground and background colors meets WCAG 2 AA minimum contrast ratio thresholds

rule_ids.help: <dl> elements must only directly contain properly-ordered <dt> and <dd> groups, <script>, <template> or <div> elements
rule_ids.description: Ensure <dl> elements are structured correctly

rule_ids.help: Headings should not be empty
rule_ids.description: Ensure headings have discernible text

rule_ids.help: Frames with focusable content must not have tabindex=-1
rule_ids.description: Ensure <frame> and <iframe> elements with focusable content do not have tabindex=-1

rule_ids.help: Frames must have an accessible name
rule_ids.description: Ensure <iframe> and <frame> elements have an accessible name

rule_ids.help: Heading levels should only increase by one
rule_ids.description: Ensure the order of headings is semantically correct

rule_ids.help: <html> element must have a lang attribute
rule_ids.description: Ensure every HTML document has a lang attribute

rule_ids.help: Images must have alternative text
rule_ids.description: Ensure elements have alternative text or a role of none or presentation

rule_ids.help: Alternative text of images should not be repeated as text
rule_ids.description: Ensure image alternative is not repeated as text

rule_ids.help: Form elements must have labels
rule_ids.description: Ensure every form element has a label

rule_ids.help: Form elements should have a visible label
rule_ids.description: Ensure that every form element has a visible label and is not solely labeled using hidden labels, or the title or aria-describedby attributes

rule_ids.help: Banner landmark should not be contained in another landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the banner landmark is at top level

rule_ids.help: Aside should not be contained in another landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the complementary landmark or aside is at top level

rule_ids.help: Contentinfo landmark should not be contained in another landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the contentinfo landmark is at top level

rule_ids.help: Main landmark should not be contained in another landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the main landmark is at top level

rule_ids.help: Document should not have more than one banner landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the document has at most one banner landmark

rule_ids.help: Document should not have more than one contentinfo landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the document has at most one contentinfo landmark

rule_ids.help: Document should not have more than one main landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the document has at most one main landmark

rule_ids.help: Document should have one main landmark
rule_ids.description: Ensure the document has a main landmark

rule_ids.help: Landmarks should have a unique role or role/label/title (i.e. accessible name) combination
rule_ids.description: Ensure landmarks are unique

rule_ids.help: Links must have discernible text
rule_ids.description: Ensure links have discernible text

rule_ids.help: <ul> and <ol> must only directly contain <li>, <script> or <template> elements
rule_ids.description: Ensure that lists are structured correctly

rule_ids.help: <li> elements must be contained in a <ul> or <ol>
rule_ids.description: Ensure <li> elements are used semantically

rule_ids.help: Zooming and scaling must not be disabled
rule_ids.description: Ensure <meta name="viewport"> does not disable text scaling and zooming

rule_ids.help: Users should be able to zoom and scale the text up to 500%
rule_ids.description: Ensure <meta name="viewport"> can scale a significant amount

rule_ids.help: Interactive controls must not be nested
rule_ids.description: Ensure interactive controls are not nested as they are not always announced by screen readers or can cause focus problems for assistive technologies

rule_ids.help: Page should contain a level-one heading
rule_ids.description: Ensure that the page, or at least one of its frames contains a level-one heading

rule_ids.help: Ensure elements marked as presentational are consistently ignored
rule_ids.description: Elements marked as presentational should not have global ARIA or tabindex to ensure all screen readers ignore them

rule_ids.help: All page content should be contained by landmarks
rule_ids.description: Ensure all page content is contained by landmarks

rule_ids.help: [role="img"] elements must have an alternative text
rule_ids.description: Ensure [role="img"] elements have alternative text

rule_ids.help: Scrollable region must have keyboard access
rule_ids.description: Ensure elements that have scrollable content are accessible by keyboard

rule_ids.help: Select element must have an accessible name
rule_ids.description: Ensure select element has an accessible name

rule_ids.help: <svg> elements with an img role must have an alternative text
rule_ids.description: Ensure <svg> elements with an img, graphics-document or graphics-symbol role have an accessible text

rule_ids.help: Elements should not have tabindex greater than zero
rule_ids.description: Ensure tabindex attribute values are not greater than 0

rule_ids.help: lang attribute must have a valid value
rule_ids.description: Ensure lang attributes have valid values
